Description:

This patch adds support to use diferent IP address, one to handle the RTP data streaming and another to handle SIP calls using UDP protocol.


 1. Get the source for Asterisk 1.8.3.2 from:
 
 http://downloads.asterisk.org/pub/telephony/asterisk/old-releases/asterisk-1.8.3.2.tar.gz
 
 
 2. Untar the Asterisk 1.8.3.2
 
 $ tar -zxvf asterisk-1.8.3.2.tar.gz
 
 
 3. Add the app WMS to asterisk
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-app-wms.patch
 
 
 4. Add the codec AMR
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-codec-amr.patch
 
 
 5. Add the SMRA support
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-smra-support.patch


 6. Add the feature reject mode
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-reject-mode.patch 
 
 7. Add the multiple IP support
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-udp-rtp-address-support.patch 
 
 8. Build Asterisk
 
 $ cd asterisk-1.8.3.2
 $ ./configure
 $ make